ul.li: Critical Boundary: A message of 55 bytes fits length in its last block. A message of 56 bytes overflows to an additional block.
Endianness: Length is written as 8 bytes, Big-Endian ($msg_len \gg 56 \dots msg_len \gg 0$).

text.tspan: Block A: zero-fill buf to 64; compress
Block B: memset buf[0..55]=0; write Length BE to buf[56..63]
